    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-02-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-02-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="529"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/2–951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation to the Torquay
                            Conference</gloss>, at Torquay, England</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-02-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 9, 1951—6 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>367. Interagency mtg held, with reps of State, <gloss target="#t_Treas1"
                        >Treas</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_Agric1">Agric</gloss>, <gloss
                        target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>, Labor, Commerce and <gloss target="#t_TarCom1"
                        >TarCom</gloss> present, to reconsider appropriate policy re Van
                    Blankenstein proposals in light House action on Trade Agreements Act. Agreed
                    that in view urgency completing Torquay bilateral negots at earliest possible
                    date and in view impaired US ability urge constructive action by other
                    countries, we can no longer pursue previous plan to press strongly for widest
                    possible <gloss target="#t_MN1">MN</gloss> tariff reductions at Torquay. Since
                    way must still be found to provide basis for <gloss target="#t_Benelux1"
                        >Benelux</gloss> signature to Torquay protocol, agreed that chief US
                    objective shld be to help in reaching some area agreement at Torquay sufficient
                    to provide such basis. Discretion to choose among courses action most likely
                    achieve these objectives placed in del. Hope you can defer any final decisions
                    at Torquay which wld prejudice this general approach, until Corse arrives early
                    next week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
